ufficiency%20in%20the%20food%20and%20crop%20market.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThis%20also%20demands%20huge%20%5Bamounts%20of%5D%20water%2C%20and%20for%20that%2C%20people%20drill%20wells.%20The%20rest%20of%20the%20pumped%20groundwater%20is%20nearly%207%25%2C%20used%20in%20crop%20fields%2C%20greenhouse%20vegetation%20cropping%2C%20fruits%2C%20and%20other%20crops%20not%20earlier%20grown%20in%20the%20region.%20Groundwater%20is%20also%20pumped%20by%20the%20hotel%20and%20guesthouse%20owners%20as%20they%20require%20fresh%20water%20for%20the%20tourists%20round%20the%20year%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20920px)%20100vw%2C%20920px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F09%2FLeh-groundwater-2-Reach-Ladakh-1726237897.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22920%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20growing%20demand%20for%20water%20in%20Leh%20requires%20better%20solutions.%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F09%2FLeh-groundwater-2-Reach-Ladakh-1726237897.jpg%20920w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F09%2FLeh-groundwater-2-Reach-Ladakh-1726237897-300x200.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F09%2FLeh-groundwater-2-Reach-Ladakh-1726237897-500x333.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F09%2FLeh-groundwater-2-Reach-Ladakh-1726237897-768x512.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F09%2FLeh-groundwater-2-Reach-Ladakh-1726237897-150x100.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-366005%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22613%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EThe%20growing%20demand%20for%20water%20in%20Leh%20requires%20better%20solutions.%20(Image%20courtesy%20Reach%20Ladakh)%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3ELeveraging%20local%20knowledge%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGiven%20the%20growing%20dependence%20on%20groundwater%20in%20local%20agriculture%20for%20growing%20water-intensive%20crops%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20necessary%20to%20hark%20back%20to%20traditional%20systems%20of%20water%20management.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20Dr%20Chorol%20notes%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20people%20of%20Ladakh%20have%20developed%20an%20incredibly%20sophisticated%20traditional%20ecological%20knowledge%20over%20generations%20of%20living%20in%20this%20harsh%2C%20high-altitude%20environment.%20Their%20intimate%20understanding%20of%20local%20hydrology%2C%20innovative%20irrigation%20techniques%2C%20and%20resource-efficient%20architectural%20designs%20are%20truly%20remarkable.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CTo%20elaborate%20on%20leveraging%20local%20knowledge%20systems%20for%20sustainable%20water%20use%20practices%2C%20we%20can%20draw%20valuable%20insights%20from%20traditional%20water%20management%20systems%20like%20those%20found%20in%20Ladakh.%20For%20instance%2C%20the%20Ladakhi%20system%20of%20appointing%20a%20%3Cem%3Echhur-pon%3C%2Fem%3E%20or%20%E2%80%98water%20lord%E2%80%99%20selected%20by%20villagers%20demonstrates%20how%20local%20communities%20can%20effectively%20govern%20their%20water%20resources.%20This%20model%20could%20be%20adapted%20to%20empower%20local%20water%20committees%20in%20other%20regions.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20how%20does%20water%20traditionally%20flow%20in%20rural%20habitations%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%202006%20paper%20titled%20%3Cem%3E%E2%80%98Traditional%20irrigation%20and%20water%20distribution%20system%20in%20Ladakh%E2%80%99%20%3C%2Fem%3Efor%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fladakh.iisdindia.in%2Ffd%2FTraditional%2520Irrigation%2520and%2520Water%2520Distribution%2520System%2520in%2520Ladakh.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20Indian%20Journal%20of%20Traditional%20Knowledge%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20authors%20Dorjey%20Angchuk%20and%20Premlata%20Singh%20explain%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20melted%20snow%20water%20from%20various%20rivulets%2C%20called%20%3Cem%3Ekangs-chhu%3C%2Fem%3E%20(ice%20water)%20merging%20at%20some%20point%20forms%20a%20%3Cem%3Etogpo%3C%2Fem%3E%20(stream)%20that%20flows%20through%20a%20valley%20touching%20many%20villages%20connected%20by%20the%20channel%2C%20called%20%3Cem%3Ema-yur%3C%2Fem%3E%20(mother%20channel).%20It%20is%20built%20along%20a%20mountainside%20that%20forms%20its%20retaining%20wall%2C%20and%20is%20lined%20with%20clay%20to%20hold%20the%20water.%20This%20is%20termed%20the%20Ladakhi%20version%20of%20a%20dyke.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CAt%20some%20places%20rocks%20are%20broken%20to%20allow%20the%20passage%20of%20water%20or%20else%20where%20the%20rocks%20are%20too%20hard%2C%20a%20hollow%20poplar%20or%20willow%20trunk%2C%20called%20%3Cem%3Eva-to%3C%2Fem%3E%20is%20cut%20into%20two%20equal%20halves%20to%20allow%20the%20water%20easy%20passage.%20Water%20from%20the%3Cem%3E%20ma-yur%3C%2Fem%3E%20is%20further%20diverted%20into%20yu-ra%20(small%20canals)%2C%20which%20irrigates%20the%20fields.%20The%20point%20from%20where%20%3Cem%3Etogpo%3C%2Fem%3E%20water%20is%20diverted%20into%20%3Cem%3Ema-yur%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20and%20%3Cem%3Ema-yur%3C%2Fem%3E%20water%20into%20%3Cem%3Eyu-ra%3C%2Fem%3E%20is%20called%20%3Cem%3Eyurgo%3C%2Fem%3E%3B%20and%20ska%20is%20the%20point%20from%20where%20%3Cem%3Eyu-ra%3C%2Fem%3E%20water%20is%20diverted%20to%20the%20field.%20Water%20in%20the%20%3Cem%3Eska%20%3C%2Fem%3Eis%20further%20guided%20through%20channels%20known%20as%20%3Cem%3Esnang%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20which%20carry%20the%20water%20into%20the%20field.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201024px)%20100vw%2C%201024px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F09%2F03-Cultivated-land-of-sakti-Dawa-Dolma-Village-Square-1726237983.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%20alt%