s%20is%20directed%20into%20a%20network%20of%20canals.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EEach%20section%20of%20the%20village%20is%20allocated%20water%20for%20irrigation%20on%20a%20rotational%20basis%2C%20typically%20for%20a%20set%20number%20of%20hours%20or%20days.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EThe%20%3Cem%3Echhur-pon%3C%2Fem%3E%20is%20responsible%20for%20opening%20and%20closing%20the%20water%20channels%20to%20ensure%20fair%20distribution.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EThis%20rotation%20is%20usually%20determined%20by%20the%20size%20of%20land%20holdings%2C%20with%20larger%20farms%20receiving%20proportionally%20more%20water%20time.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EThe%20system%20is%20flexible%20and%20can%20be%20adjusted%20based%20on%20seasonal%20water%20availability%20and%20crop%20needs.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3ECommunity%20meetings%20are%20held%20to%20discuss%20and%20resolve%20any%20disputes%20or%20changes%20needed%20in%20the%20water%20allocation.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIndigenous%20engineering%20techniques%2C%20such%20as%20Ladakh%E2%80%99s%20intricate%20canal%20systems%20(%3Cem%3Ema-yur%2C%20yu-ra%3C%2Fem%3E)%2C%20showcase%20local%20ingenuity%20in%20adapting%20to%20challenging%20terrains.%20By%20studying%20and%20applying%20such%20local%20engineering%20knowledge%2C%20we%20can%20develop%20context-appropriate%20irrigation%20solutions%20elsewhere%2C%E2%80%9D%20explains%20Dr%20Chorol.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20how%20do%20these%20intricate%20canal%20systems%20work%3F%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3EMa-yur%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cstrong%3E(mother%20canal)%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cul%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-list%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EThis%20is%20the%20main%20canal%20that%20diverts%20water%20from%20glacier-fed%20streams.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EIt%20is%20typically%20built%20along%20contour%20lines%20to%20maintain%20a%20gentle%20slope%20for%20water%20flow.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EThe%3Cem%3E%20ma-yur%3C%2Fem%3E%20is%20often%20lined%20with%20stones%20to%20prevent%20seepage%20and%20erosion.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EIt%20can%20stretch%20for%20several%20kilometres%2C%20bringing%20water%20to%20multiple%20villages.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3EYu-ra%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cstrong%3E(subsidiary%20canals)%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cul%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-list%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EThese%20are%20smaller%20channels%20that%20branch%20off%20from%20the%20ma-yur.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Cem%3EYu-ra%3C%2Fem%3E%20distributes%20water%20to%20individual%20fields%20or%20clusters%20of%20fields.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EThey%20are%20designed%20to%20follow%20the%20natural%20topography%2C%20minimising%20the%20need%20for%20pumping.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EFarmers%20use%20simple%20gates%20or%20stones%20to%20control%20water%20flow%20into%20their%20fields.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20systems%20allow%20locals%20to%20adapt%20to%20challenging%20terrains%20by%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cul%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-list%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EUtilising%20gravity%20for%20water%20distribution%2C%20reducing%20the%20need%20for%20energy-intensive%20pumping.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EMaximising%20the%20use%20of%20limited%20water%20resources%20in%20an%20arid%20environment.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EPreventing%20soil%20erosion%20through%20careful%20canal%20placement%20and%20construction.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EAllowing%20cultivation%20on%20steep%20hillsides%20through%20terrace%20farming.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20traditional%20water%20storage%20methods%2C%20like%20the%20use%20of%20ponds%20(%3Cem%3Erdzing%3C%2Fem%3E)%20in%20Ladakh%2C%20can%20be%20revived%20and%20improved%20to%20enhance%20water%20security%20in%20water-scarce%20regions%2C%20notes%20Dr%20Chorol.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIndividual%20families%20rarely%20construct%20their%20own%20pond.%20Every%20year%20at%20the%20beginning%20of%3Cem%3E%20spit%3C%2Fem%3E%20(spring)%2C%20ponds%20are%20cleared%20of%20silts.%20Villagers%20collectively%20undertake%20the