e%20the%20company%20has%20collectively%20seen%20100%2C000%20automated%20rides%20a%20week.%20Contrast%20that%20to%20Tesla%2C%20which%20has%20yet%20to%20prove%20its%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftesla-fsd-full-self-driving-san-francisco-sunset-district-testing-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFull-Self%20Driving%20system%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20fully%20autonomous%20despite%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felon-musk-history-of-full-self-driving-promise-2022-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMusk's%20repeated%20proclamations%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20the%20company%20is%20almost%20there.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTesla%20has%20nothing%20approaching%20a%20self-driving%20car%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKevin%20Chen%2C%20a%20former%20software%20engineer%20for%20the%20autonomous%20driving%20industry%20who%20has%20used%20both%20Tesla's%20FSD%20and%20Waymo%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20he%20sees%20some%20validity%20to%20Karpathy's%20sentiment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20viewed%20Tesla%20as%20a%20%26quot%3Bpioneer%26quot%3B%20in%20using%20machine%20learning%20for%20its%20autonomous%20driving%20software.%20Given%20that%20the%20company%20has%20millions%20of%20cars%20on%20the%20road%20today%2C%20he%20said%20it's%20ahead%20in%20manufacturing%20autonomous%20hardware%20at%20scale.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20he%20also%20argued%20that%20Tesla's%20autonomous%20hardware%20hasn't%20solved%20the%20driverless%20equation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20don't%20know%20if%20the%20camera-only%20approach%20is%20sufficient%20to%20reach%20driverless%20quality%20with%20the%20current%20state%20of%20machine%20learning%20and%20AI%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BSo%20then%20the%20big%20question%20is%3A%20Are%20you%20waiting%20for%20some%20AI%20breakthrough%20to%20solve%20this%20problem%3F%20Or%20maybe%20you're%20waiting%20for%20some%20chipmaking%20breakthrough%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWaymo%2C%20on%20t