particularly%20in%20areas%20tied%20to%20socialization.%3Cp%3EInstitute%20for%20Learning%20and%20Brain%20Sciences%2C%20University%20of%20Washington%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EA%20new%20study%20found%20that%20teen%20girls'%20brains%20aged%20faster%20during%20the%20pandemic.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EResearchers%20measured%20cortical%20thinning%2C%20a%20natural%20process%20that%20can%20be%20accelerated%20by%20stress.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EQuicker%20cortical%20thinning%20is%20linked%20to%20higher%20risks%20of%20anxiety%20and%20depression.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20week%2C%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pnas.org%2Fdoi%2Ffull%2F10.1073%2Fpnas.2403200121%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enew%20scientific%20paper%3C%2Fa%3E%20sent%20a%20ripple%20through%20the%20world%20of%20child%20psychology.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EResearchers%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Washington%20published%20brain%20scans%20of%20teenagers%20taken%20three%20years%20apart%2C%20in%202018%20and%202021.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20team%20expected%20significant%20findings%2C%20since%20the%20second%20scans%20were%20taken%20after%20all%20of%20the%20kids%20had%20their%20lives%20suddenly%20upended%20and%20socially%20stunted%20by%20COVID%20lockdowns.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20hypothesized%20that%20girls%20would%20be%20more%20impacted%2C%20because%20they're%20more%20reliant%20on%20peer%20relationships%20for%20emotional%20support%20than%20teen%20boys.%20But%20%26quot%3Bwe%20didn't%20expect%20it%20to%20be%20as%20dramatic%20a%20difference%2C%26quot%3B%20lead%20author%20Dr.%20Neva%20Corrigan%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20average%20acceleration%20for%20teen%20girls%20was%204.2%20years%2C%20compared%20to%201.4%20for%20boys.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20more%20research%20is%20needed%2C%20the%20study%20offers%20a%20glimpse%20into%20the%20effects%20the%20pandemic%20had%20on%20brain%20development.%20It%20comes%20at%20a%20time%20when%20teen%20girls%20have%20seen%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcdc-report-teen-girls-alarming-rates-sadness-hopelessness-sexual-violence-2023-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esharp%20rise%20in%20sadness%20and%20hopelessness%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20often%20attributed%20to%20social%20media%20use.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22c81b7065-67f7-4f59-9455-c4636815bed5%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EIsolation%20may%20have%20played%20a%20role%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20original%20intention%20of%20the%20study%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ewas%20to%20track%20typical%20adolescent%20brain%20development%2C%20Corrigan%2C%20who%20specializes%20in%20MRI%20data%20acquisition%20and%20analysis%2C%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Etold%20BI.%20In%202018%2C%20her%20team%20took%20MRI%20data%20from%20160%20adolescents%20ages%209%2C%2011%2C%2013%2C%2015%2C%20and%2017%2C%20and%20planned%20to%20follow%20up%20at%20a%20later%20date.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20after%20the%20pandemic%2C%20%26quot%3Bwe%20realized%20that%20we%20could%20no%20longer%20call%20this%20typical%20development%2C%26quot%3B%20Corrigan%20said.%20%26quot%3BThese%20kids%20had%20undergone%20a%20huge%20change%20in%20their%20lives.%26quot%3B%20Her%20team%20knew%20they%20had%20a%20unique%20opportunity%20to%20examine%20how%20aspects%20of%20the%20pandemic%2C%20such%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpublic-teacher-homeschool-own-kids-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eremote%20learning%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20affected%20the%20brain.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202021%2C%20about%20130%20of%20the%20subjects%20returned%20for%20more%20testing.%20The%20team%20measured%20cortical%20thinning%2C%20a%20natural%20process%20that%20usually%20begins%20in%20late%20childhood%20and%20is%20believed%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2Fpmc%2Farticles%2FPMC3791607%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eimprove%20cognitive%20performance%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20age%20acceleration%20was%20more%20than%20double%20the%20size%20in%20teen%20girls%2C%20and%20the%20regions%20most%20impacted%20were%20all%20related%20to%20social%20cognition%2C%20such%20as%20facial%20recognition%20and%20language%20comprehension.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBecause%20females%20generally%20rely%20more%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2F17328705%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erelationships%20for%20emotional%20support%3C%2Fa%3E%20than%20males%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmodern-loneliness%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eloneliness%3C%2Fa%3E%20during%20the%20pandemic%20could%20have%20caused%20teen%20girls%20more%20stress%2C%20speeding%20up%20their%20cortical%20thinning.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22ca6c015e-1e33-410a-957c-fdee9576f795%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ECortical%20thinning%20isn't%20always%20negative%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ECorrigan%20said%20there's%20a%20lot%20we%20still%20don't%20know%20about%20cortical%20thinning%2C%20such%20as%20whether%20it's%20reversible.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20she%20said%20past%20studies%20have%20shown%20that%20accelerated%20cortical%20thinning%20can%20put%20people%20at%20higher%20risk%20for%20neurodegenerative%20disorders%20in%20old%20age%2C%20such%20as%20Alzheimer's%20and%20Parkinson's.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20can%20also%20increase%20the%20odds%20of%20developing%20psychiatric%20disorders%20such%20as%20depression%20or%20anxiety.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20same%20time%2C%20quicker%20brain%20aging%20isn't%20necessarily%20all%20bad.%20It's%20believed%20that%20the%20cortex%20thins%20to%20reduce%20the%20effect%20the%20environment%20has%20on%20brain%20development%2C%20Corrigan%20said.%20If%20the%20brain%20is%20less%20vulnerable%20to%20external%20stressors%2C%20%26quot%3Bthat%20could%20make%20these%20kids%20a%20little%20bit%20more%20resilient%20to%20stress%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2247b59dfa-19bd-494b-98ab-6151b36b2682%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EThere%20are%20still%20many%20unknowns%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBradley%20S.%20Peterson%2C%20a%20pediatric%20psychiatrist%20at%20Children's%20Hospital%20Los%20Angeles%20who%20wasn't%20part%20of%20the%20study%2C%20told%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2024%2F09%2F09%2Fhealth%2Fteen-brains-pandemic-girls.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20New%20York%20Times%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20it%20had%20some%20limitations.%20One%20was%20that%20the%20data%20came%20from%20different%20subsets%20of%20the%20group%2C%20rather%20than%20measuring%20each%20individual's%20brain%20changes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20study%20also%20didn't%20track%20the%20participants'%20individual%20habits%2C%20so%20it%20can't%20confirm%20if%20other%20elements%20of%20the%20pandemic%2C%20such%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsurgeon-general-social-media-warning-label-mental-health-crisis-children-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eincreased%20screen%20time%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20contributed%20to%20quicker%20cortical%20thinning.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECorrigan%20said%20the%20biggest%20takeaway%20for%20parents%20is%20to%20be%20mindful%20of%20the%20potential%20risks%20of%20their%20teens%20developing%20anxiety%20or%20depression.%20%26quot%3BPerhaps%20they%20can%20help%20stave%20that%20off%20by%20talking%20to%20their%20kids%20and%20providing%20emotional%20support%20for%20them.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fteen-girls-brain-aged-faster-pandemic-anxiety-depression-2024-9%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1726261640000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66e4926fcfb7f307e5718940%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fteen-girls-brain-aged-faster-pandemic-anxiety-depression-2024-9%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20study%20found%20that%20teen%20girls'%20brains%20aged%204.2%20years%20faster%20than%20average%20during%20the%20pandemic.%20They%20might%20be%20at%20higher%20risk%20for%20anxiety%20and%20depression.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22jpugachevsky%40insider.com%20(Julia%20Pugachevsky)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A20%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fteen-girls-brain-aged-faster-pandemic-anxiety-depression-2024-9%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22JD%20Vance%20said%20he%20would%20'consider'%20privatizing%20some%20veteran%20healthcare%20services%20if%20elected%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223712%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22JD%20Vance%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66a56c49a0fc5856d597fe85%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222472%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EOhio%20Sen.%20JD%20Vance%20was%20first%20elected%20to%20office%20in%202022.%3Cp%3EAP%20Photo%2FJulia%20Nikhinson%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EGOP%20VP%20candidate%20JD%20Vance%20said%20he%20would%20consider%20privatizing%20some%20veteran%20healthcare%20if%20elected.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EDemocrats%20have%20billed%20the%20GOP-led%20effort%20as%20a%20bid%20to%20replace%20VA%20funding%20with%20private-sector%20profits.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHarris'%20campaign%20accused%20Vance%2C%20a%20former%20Marine%2C%20of%20turning%20VA%20services%20into%20%26quot%3Ba%20business%20opportunity.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ERepublican%20vice%20presidential%20nominee%20Sen.%20JD%20Vance%20expressed%20support%20for%20expanding%20veterans'%20ability%20to%20use%20private%20doctors%20in%20a%20podcast%20interview%20this%20week.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fyoutu.be%2FHrgmwtpAsWc%3Fsi%3DC27O-DnN9HJlH1tX%26t%3D2649%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eappearance%20on%20the%20Shawn%20Ryan%20Show%20released%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20Wednesday%2C%20Vance%20was%20asked%20by%20the%20host%2C%20a%20former%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mi