ure%20with%20our%20list%20of%20partners%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20more%20details).%20However%2C%20our%20opinions%20are%20our%20own.%20See%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fpersonal-finance-editorial-standards%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehow%20we%20rate%20products%20and%20services%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20help%20you%20make%20smart%20decisions%20with%20your%20money.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Clari%20Nolet%2C%20Asad%20Gourani%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F608c25f235c46f0018c0b893%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EFinancial%20planners%20Clari%20Nolet%20(left)%20and%20Asad%20Gourani.%3Cp%3EClari%20Nolet%2C%20Sudeep%20Studio%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EFinancial%20planners%20say%20millennials%20have%20a%20few%20not-so-great%20spending%20habits.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3ESpending%20on%20convenience%20and%20big-ticket%20items%20is%20OK%2C%20but%20not%20if%20they%20don't%20fit%20your%20budget.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3ESetting%20financial%20goals%20and%20automating%20your%20bills%20before%20spending%20on%20wants%20can%20help.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EWe're%20all%20guilty%20of%20making%20the%20%26quot%3Bwrong%26quot%3B%20spending%20choices%20from%20time%20to%20time%2C%20and%20millennials%20are%20no%20exception.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20financial%20planners%2C%20there%20are%20two%20things%20millennials%20overspend%20on%20way%20too%20often.%20Below%2C%20they%20share%20the%20top%20ways%20they've%20had%20to%20help%20their%20younger%20clients%20curb%20their%20spending.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E1.%20Spending%20on%20convenience%C2%A0%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EFinancial%20planner%20Clari%20Nolet%2C%20of%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fteamhewins.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETeam%20Hewins%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20says%20millennials%20have%20gotten%20used%20to%20the%20culture%20of%20instant%20gratification.%20The%20result%20is%20a%20tendency%20to%20spend%20on%20services%20that%20make%20things%20quick%20and%20easy%2C%20like%20food%20delivery%20apps%20that%20bring%20your%20meal%20right%20to%20your%20door%2C%20and%20fast.%20These%20services%20can%20be%20much%20more%20costly%20than%20cooking%20at%20home%20or%20even%20picking%20up%20the%20food%20yourself.%20And%2C%20they%20can%20add%20up%20quickly%20over%20the%20span%20of%20a%20month.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFinancial%20planners%20say%20it's%20OK%20to%20spend%20your%20money%20on%20these%20things%2C%20but%20it%20becomes%20a%20problem%20when%20it%20doesn't%20fit%20into%20your%20budget%20or%20you're%20not%20meeting%20your%20financial%20goals.%20Having%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fbanking%2Fwhat-is-an-emergency-fund%5C%22%3Eemergency%20fund%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0in%20place%20or%20contributing%20to%20your%20401(k)%20should%20be%20prioritized%20before%20considering%20how%20much%20you%20can%20or%20should%20be%20spending%20on%20these%20extra%20services.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20most%20people%2C%20not%20just%20millennials%2C%20don't%20really%20have%20a%20budget%20and%20don't%20know%20how%20much%20they%20spend.%20They%20have%20an%20estimate%20in%20their%20mind.%20And%20if%20you%20ask%20somebody%20what%20%5Bthey%5D%20spend%2C%20they%20can%20give%20you%20an%20answer%2C%20but%20if%20you%20really%20dig%20into%20the%20details%2C%20you%20find%20that%20they're%20fooling%20themselves.%20The%20amount%20that%20they're%20spending%20is%20typically%20a%20lot%20more%20than%20they%20think%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Nolet.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20recommends%20having%20financial%20goals%20in%20place%20so%20you%20know%20what%20you're%20saving%20toward.%20This%20will%20help%20you%20figure%20out%20your%20discretionary%20spending%20budget%20once%20you've%20covered%20your%20priorities.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20first%20things%20to%20consider%20saving%20toward%20is%20an%20emergency%20fundthat%20can%20cover%20your%20expenses%20in%20the%20event%20of%20a%20job%20loss%20or%20emergency.%20Because%20of%20the%20job%20losses%20witnessed%20after%20the%20COVID-19%20pandemic%2C%20Nolet%20says%20you%20should%20now%20aim%20to%20save%20anywhere%20between%20six%20and%2012%20months%20of%20expenses.%20The%20next%20thing%20to%20do%20is%20contribute%20to%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Finvesting%2Fwhat-is-401k%5C%22%3E401(k)%3C%2Fa%3E%20up%20to%20or%20above%20the%20employer's%20match%20to%20take%20advantage%20of%20that%20free%20money.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Caside%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fhow-to-find-financial-advisor%5C%22%3EFinding%20a%20financial%20advisor%3C%2Fa%3E%20doesn't%20have%20to%20be%20hard.%20SmartAsset's%20free%20tool%20matches%20you%20with%20up%20to%20three%20fiduciary%20financial%20advisors%20that%20serve%20your%20area%20in%20minutes.%20Each%20advisor%20has%20been%20vetted%20by%20SmartAsset%20and%20is%20held%20to%20a%20fiduciary%20standard%20to%20act%20in%20your%20best%20interests.%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsmartasset.com%2Fretirement%2Ffind-a-financial-planner%3Futm_source%3Dbusinessinsider%26utm_medium%3Dcpc%26utm_campaign%3Dbus__falc_bicontent%26utm_content%3DBI%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20Start%20your%20search%20now.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Faside%3E%3Ch2%3E2.%20Spending%20on%20big-ticket%20items%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EFinancial%20planner%20Asad%20Gourani%20of%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.agwealthm.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAG%20Wealth%20Management%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20less%20concerned%20about%20millennials'%20day-to-day%20expenses.%20He's%20more%20focused%20on%20bills%20that%20are%20recurring%20and%20aren't%20flexible%2C%20such%20as%20a%20mortgage%20payment%20or%20a%20lease%20for%20a%20new%20car.%20These%20kinds%20of%20expenses%20are%20more%20difficult%20to%20cut%20out%20once%20you've%20made%20the%20purchase.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAfter%20years%20of%20working%20almost%20exclusively%20with%20millennials%2C%20we%20noticed%20that%20the%20big%20theme%20is%20that%20millennials%20tend%20to%20spend%20a%20lot%20more%20on%20experiences%20rather%20%5Bthan%5D%20material%20items%20compared%20to%20prior%20generations%2C%20which%20is%20a%20very%20positive%20thing%20as%20long%20as%20it%20falls%20within%20their%20means%2C%26quot%3B%20Gourani%20tells%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BWhere%20the%20problem%20generally%20lies%20is%20with%20un-calculated%20spending%20habits%20and%20lack%20of%20planning%20especially%20around%20bigger-ticket%20items.%20Trust%20me%2C%20skipping%20on%20avocado%20toast%20and%20lattes%20won't%20make%20much%20of%20a%20difference%20on%20your%20finances.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGourani's%20approach%20is%20to%20work%20with%20clients%20to%20help%20shift%20their%20mindset%20so%20that%20they%20don't%20feel%20like%20they're%20being%20restricted%20by%20a%20budget.%20This%20means%20developing%20a%20conscious%20spending%20plan%20that%20they%20are%20comfortable%20with%20%E2%80%94%20and%20is%20within%20their%20means%20%E2%80%94%20and%20then%20automating%20payments%2C%20such%20as%20housing%2C%20utilities%2C%20student%20loans%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Finvesting%2Fbest-retirement-plans%5C%22%3Eretirement%20plan%3C%2Fa%3E%20contributions.%20Then%2C%20whatever%20is%20left%20can%20be%20spent%20%26quot%3Bguilt-free.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECertain%20payments%2C%20such%20as%20retirement%20contributions%20or%20savings%2C%20can%20be%20done%20directly%20through%20your%20employer.%20For%20mortgage%2C%20credit%20card%2C%20and%20loan%20repayments%2C%20those%20can%20typically%20be%20set%20up%20through%20your%20bank.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20analogy%20we%20like%20to%20give%20is%20that%20budgets%20